TITLE:BAX vs Hugo, Jekyll, and 11ty - Which One to Choose?
DATE:11 July 2026
IMG:https://placehold.co/800x400/0f172a/ffffff?text=BAX+vs+Others
DESC:Compare BAX with Hugo, Jekyll, and 11ty. Find out which static site generator is right for your project.
TAGS:bax hugo jekyll 11ty comparison static-site

H2:Why BAX is Different
P:BAX is not trying to replace Hugo, Jekyll, or 11ty. It's a different tool for different use cases. BAX focuses on simplicity, zero dependencies, and ease of use.

P:Think of BAX as the "bicycle" of static site generators - simple, easy to use, and perfect for getting where you need to go without the complexity of a "car".

HR:

H2:Quick Comparison

H3:BAX vs Hugo
UL:
LI:BAX: Zero dependencies, very easy to learn, builds in milliseconds
LI:Hugo: Requires Go, steep learning curve, faster but complex
/UL:

H3:BAX vs Jekyll
UL:
LI:BAX: Runs on any platform, simple .zet format, lightweight
LI:Jekyll: Requires Ruby, uses Markdown, heavier and slower
/UL:

H3:BAX vs 11ty
UL:
LI:BAX: No dependencies, ultra-simple, fast builds
LI:11ty: Requires Node.js, flexible but more complex setup
/UL:

HR:

H2:When to Use BAX
UL:
LI:Simple personal blogs
LI:Portfolio websites
LI:Documentation sites
LI:Landing pages
LI:Small business websites
LI:When you hate installing dependencies
LI:When you want to build fast without complexity
/UL:

H2:When to Use Hugo
UL:
LI:Large sites with thousands of pages
LI:Complex content structures
LI:Multi-language sites
LI:Professional projects
/UL:

H2:When to Use Jekyll
UL:
LI:GitHub Pages native support
LI:Blog-focused sites
LI:Ruby developers
LI:Traditional blogging
/UL:

H2:When to Use 11ty
UL:
LI:JavaScript developers
LI:Complex sites needing flexibility
LI:Multiple template languages
LI:Modern web development
/UL:

HR:

H2:When to Choose BAX

H3:Choose BAX If:
UL:
LI:You're a beginner learning static sites
LI:You want a simple blog or personal site
LI:You hate installing dependencies
LI:You work across different operating systems
LI:You want to build fast without complexity
LI:You appreciate minimalist tools
/UL:

H3:Don't Choose BAX If:
UL:
LI:You need thousands of pages
LI:You require complex plugins
LI:You need multiple themes
LI:You're building a large enterprise site
/UL:

HR:

H2:Our Recommendation
P:If you're building a simple blog, portfolio, or documentation site, choose BAX.

P:If you're building a large, complex site with thousands of pages, choose Hugo.

P:If you're already a Ruby or Node.js developer, consider Jekyll or 11ty.

BLOCKQUOTE:"The best tool is the one that helps you ship your work. Choose simplicity over complexity when you can."

HR:

H2:Start with BAX Today
P:Try BAX for your next project:

CODE:git clone https://github.com/mesinkasir/bax.git
CODE:cd bax
CODE:bax.bat  # Windows
CODE:./bax.sh # Linux/Mac

